    <string-array name="science_text_medical">
        <item>A large <a href = "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19996993">long-term study</a> with 7744 participants looked into sedentary behavior and risk of cardiovascular disease mortality in men over a 21 year period.  It found sedentary behavior increased risk of death from cardiovascular disease by 64 percent to percent.</item>
        <item>A Danish <a href = "http://sjp.sagepub.com/content/35/5/510.abstract"> medical study </a>that looked into factors which decreased life quality found sedentary lifestyles reduced the quality-adjusted life years by 7 years.</item>
        <item>A British <a href = " http://bjsm.bmj.com/content/43/2/81.full">research study</a>  found that even exercising for 30 minutes or more a day might not be enough to counteract the negative effects of sitting for prolonged periods of time.</item>
        <item>Sitting for prolonged periods of time may contribute to <a href = "http://diabetes.diabetesjournals.org/content/56/11/2655.long">metabolic diseases</a> such as diabetes and cardiovascular disease.</item>
    </string-array>
